  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/6079",
  "title": "poc(helper): recommend helper-style",
  "body": "Following concerns about having search helper users needing to import an extra package in order to use recommend, and leaking backend implementation details in our API, I made this PoC showing how much changes would be needed to wrap recommend in the helper.\r\n\r\nThis assumes the client has the `getRecommendations` method. Else we would either need to break the constructor, or add an optional argument for the recommendClient last.\r\n\r\nI tried as much as possible to match the current API, but putting everything in existing events and/or methods would need much more logic and be less performant.\r\n\r\nThe only difference for the user would be that **in addition to being able to do** `const result = await helper.getClient().getRecommendations()` they could do : \r\n\r\n```js\r\nhelper.addFrequentlyBoughtTogether().recommend();\r\nhelper.on('recommendResult', (result) => /* ... */);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis actually accentuates implementation details even more.",
